# JSON Data Formats

## JSONL Data Files (defaults/data/)

Line-delimited JSON. Two entry types:

### Node
```json
{"type":"node","name":"Hari Seldon","nodeType":"npc","metadata":["role:psychohistorian","Description: Creator of psychohistory"]}
```

Fields:
- `type`: always `"node"`
- `name`: object name (used for edge resolution by name)
- `nodeType`: must match a schema type (npc, location, faction, quest, artifact, etc.)
- `metadata`: array of strings. `"key:value"` â†’ property. Bare string â†’ tag. `"Description: ..."` â†’ description.

### Edge
```json
{"type":"edge","from":"Hari Seldon","to":"Trantor","edgeType":"lived_on"}
```

Fields:
- `type`: always `"edge"`
- `from`: source node name (must exist in same or prior import â€” see BUG-7)
- `to`: target node name
- `edgeType`: string-based relationship type (flexible, no enum restriction)

### Supported Node Types
npc, player_character, location, faction, quest, artifact, currency, skills, temporal, setting_reference, system_reference, transportation, inventory

### Import Pipeline (data_ingestion.rs)
Two-pass: collect all nodes â†’ create objects with nameâ†’ID map â†’ resolve edge names â†’ create edges.

**Known bugs:**
- BUG-6: No deduplication â€” re-importing creates duplicates
- BUG-7: Edge resolution only works within a single import session (in-memory nameâ†’ID map)

## Schema Files (defaults/schemas/)

Named `*.schema.json`. Define object types and validation rules.

```json
{
  "name": "add_npc",
  "description": "Add a new NPC to the knowledge graph",
  "properties": {
    "name": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "NPC name",
      "required": true,
      "validation": { "min_length": 1, "max_length": 100 }
    },
    "role": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "NPC role",
      "required": true,
      "validation": { "allowed_values": ["merchant", "guard", "noble"] }
    },
    "currentLocation": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Current location",
      "relationship": {
        "edgeType": "located_in",
        "targetType": "location"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### Property types
`string`, `text`, `number`, `boolean`, `array`, `object`, `reference`

### Validation rules
`min_length`, `max_length`, `min_value`, `max_value`, `pattern` (regex), `allowed_values`, `required`

### Naming convention
Files use `add_` prefix in `name` field (MCP tool convention). `SchemaIngestion` strips the prefix â€” `add_npc` becomes `npc` internally.

## Validation Commands

```bash
# Check JSON syntax
cat file.json | jq .

# Count nodes by type
jq -c 'select(.type == "node") | .nodeType' defaults/data/memory.json | sort | uniq -c

# Find edges
jq -c 'select(.type == "edge")' defaults/data/memory.json | head
```

## Sample Data

`defaults/data/memory.json`: ~220 nodes + ~312 edges from Isaac Asimov's Foundation universe. Used by CLI demo.